<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/54892524-daniel"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/54892524-daniel">Daniel</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">There&apos;s a chapter in the book called &quot;Máscaras Mexicanas&quot; (could be translated to Mexican Masks as I&apos;n not sure how is it titled on English), in this <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">There's a chapter in the book called "Máscaras Mexicanas" (could be translated to Mexican Masks as I'n not sure how is it titled on English), in this chapter Paz talks about how we disguise (Mexicans) our real emotions behind everyday "masks" between other things (don't want to ruin if if you haven't read it already).<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
