        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1348005805" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8307249628000947107">&quot;Myths and fiestas, whether secular or religious, permit man to emerge from his solitude and become one with creation&quot;<br/>Octavio Paz pulls much of this work together with this statement. Once one might squeeze around or past linear concepts of space and time, allowing for a complex (not complicated) system of thought existent in present presence, Paz&apos;s thoughts on myth and fiesta sound closer to truth&apos;s fragile being. The last paragraph does not end this work as much as it presents a beginning:<br/>&quot;Mod</span>
  <span id="freeText8307249628000947107" style="display:none">"Myths and fiestas, whether secular or religious, permit man to emerge from his solitude and become one with creation"<br />Octavio Paz pulls much of this work together with this statement. Once one might squeeze around or past linear concepts of space and time, allowing for a complex (not complicated) system of thought existent in present presence, Paz's thoughts on myth and fiesta sound closer to truth's fragile being. The last paragraph does not end this work as much as it presents a beginning:<br />"Modern man likes to pretend that his thinking is wide-awake. But this wide-awake thinking has led us into the mazes of a nightmare in which the torture chambers are endlessly repeated in the mirrors of reason. When we emerge, perhaps we will realize that we have been dreaming with our eyes open, and that the dreams of reason are intolerable. And then, perhaps, we will begin to dream once more with our eyes closed."</span>
  <a data-text-id="8307249628000947107" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
